				{
					"id": "125993",
					"author": {
						"name": "stephentramer",
						"key": "stephentramer",
						"displayName": "Stephen Tramer",
						"active": true,
						"timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
					},
					"body": "{html}<div><p>Accidentally committed fix as <a href=\n\"/projects/32238/tickets/1534\" title=\"Ticket #1534\">#1534</a>. See\nthere for details.</p>\n<p>KS Test:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Base UI-&gt;Views-&gt;Hi-Res Image Remote</li>\n<li>Should display the same image, in same bounds, at same\nresolution, as Base UI-&gt;Views-&gt;Hi Res Image 2</li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<p><strong>ABOUT REMOTE SUPPORT</strong>: We do not support\nautomatic remote detection of 2x images. You are required to check\ndisplay density (Ti.Platform.displayCaps.density) for a 'high'\nvalue to indicate a retina display. You must then also set the\n'hires' property on any image view which uses one of these images,\notherwise you may see unexpected scaling behavior.</p></div>{html}",
					"updateAuthor": {
						"name": "stephentramer",
						"key": "stephentramer",
						"displayName": "Stephen Tramer",
						"active": true,
						"timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
